  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I be myself? No matter where I am or how I am, I just can't be myself and I get very nervous",
  "response": "I'm really sorry you're feeling this way. Struggling to be yourself and feeling nervous in various situations can be challenging, but there are steps you can take to help overcome these feelings:\n\n1. **Self-Awareness and Reflection**:\n   - **Identify Triggers**: Pay attention to the situations or environments that make you feel nervous or prevent you from being yourself.\n   - **Understand Your Values**: Clarify what\u2019s important to you. When you know your values, it's easier to act in ways that are true to yourself.\n\n2. **Build Self-Confidence**:\n   - **Celebrate Small Wins**: Acknowledge and celebrate your achievements, no matter how small they may seem.\n   - **Positive Affirmations**: Remind yourself of your strengths and positive qualities regularly.\n\n3. **Practice Mindfulness and Relaxation Techniques**:\n   - **Mindfulness Meditation**: Helps you stay present and reduces anxiety about how you\u2019re perceived.\n   - **Deep Breathing Exercises**: Can calm your nervous system when you start to feel anxious.\n\n4. **Gradual Exposure**:\n   - **Step-by-Step Approach**: Start by being yourself in low-pressure situations and gradually work up to more challenging environments.\n   - **Set Manageable Goals**: For example, initiate a conversation or share something personal with someone you trust.\n\n5. **Seek Support**:\n   - **Talk to Trusted Friends or Family**: Sharing your feelings with someone you trust can provide comfort and perspective.\n   - **Join Support Groups**: Connecting with others who have similar experiences can help you feel less alone.\n\n6. **Professional Help**:\n   - **Therapy or Counseling**: A mental health professional can provide strategies tailored to your specific situation and help you work through underlying issues contributing to your nervousness.\n\n7. **Self-Compassion**:\n   - **Be Kind to Yourself**: Understand that it's okay to feel nervous and that everyone struggles with being themselves at times.\n   - **Avoid Self-Judgment**: Instead of criticizing yourself for not being able to act naturally, acknowledge your efforts to change.\n\nRemember, it's a journey, and it's okay to seek help along the way. Taking these steps can gradually help you feel more comfortable being yourself in different settings.",
